BOKS
====

Boks firmware, Python interface, and OpenSesame plug-in
Copyright (2012) Sebastiaan MathÃ´t
http://boks.cogsci.nl

ABOUT
=====
Boks is an open-source response boks, based on the Arduino. This repository
(will) contain(s) the Arduino firmware, Python interface, and OpenSesame 
plug-in.

TESTING
=======
To test the boks, load the firmware onto the Arduino using the Arduio IDE.
Connect the buttons to pins 2, 4, 7, and 8 of the Arduino. Test the Arduino
by running the test script and passing the port number to which the Arduino
is connected as parameter. For example:

> testboks /dev/ttyACM0
> testboks COM3

FILES
=====
